CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 8, 1958, reads: "Walter C. Rainey... ran well but lost." Partial article reads: "In the Fifth Legislative District, Republican Walter C. Rainey lost to Democrat Leo J. McLaughlin by slightly less than two to one. Rainey's surprising vote came from the few Republicans in 12th and 13th wards and the increased number of dissatisfied Negro Democratic votes in the district."
TitMainTitle: Republican candidate for legislature in Fifth District Walter C. Rainey, posed with fingers in victory sign in front of voting machine
